The paper deals with the problem of Android malware detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach uses deep learning techniques, specifically Autoencoder, to identify malware, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the need for effective methods to suppress the spread of malware, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of storing and processing personal data on smartphones, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
